observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require concerned officials/employees to:

adopt measures to resolve the unadjusted employee accounts with the electronic billing and collection system of the GSIS, Pag-IBIG and PhilHealth, and the failure of the personnel-in-charge to update employee accounts on their salary increments;

verify that payroll deductions align with actual employee contributions and loan amortizations before processing remittances;

ensure all premium contributions and loan amortizations are remitted within the prescribed deadlines to avoid penalties and interest charges; and

conduct monthly reconciliations of employee premium contributions and loan amortizations by comparing the GSIS, Pag-IBIG and PhilHealth billings with actual payroll deductions and remitted amounts.

To ensure that cash is available to pay the contract costs of the projects due to the contractors, we recommended that the Municipal Treasurer: 

prepare a breakdown of the main General Fund bank balance and determine the actual cash pertaining to the 20% DF;

maintain a logbook to record the receipts of 20% of the IRA and the checks issued therefrom, and; 

monitor the balance of the 20% DF and reconcile monthly the amount with the Cash in Bank account subsidiary ledger maintained by the Municipal Accountant.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, the HRMO and other Department heads concerned:

Submit justification for the hiring of  283 JO personnel;

Limit the hiring of JO personnel to complement only the office where transactions are voluminous;

Ensure that the functions and responsibilities of the JOs are well-defined and clear in their respective Contracts of Service to facilitate evaluation of work performed by the employees.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor and the designated Municipal Environment and Natural Resources Officer (MENRO) ensure the continued implementation of the LGU’s Solid Waste Management Plan through the following:

widen the coverage of the municipality’s garbage collection system;



provide personal protective equipment and training on the proper handling of wastes to all collectors/personnel handling solid wastes to ensure their safety during garbage collection.

We recommended:   

to conduct actual inventory of the land owned by the Municipality;



determine the acquisition cost of each lot and the deed of donation if warranted; 



the reconciliation of the accounting and GSO records;



the Accounting Office and GSO should keep complete records of the real properties and most importantly; 

the titling of all the parcel of lands in the name of the Municipality.

